  "market_context": "Price retraced into a 4H demand zone after a downtrend, swept liquidity below equal lows (liquidity sweep), then reversed upward, breaking two successive bearish structures on the 15m chart.",
  "key_observation": "A high-probability Change of Character formed after price swept SSL below equal lows, tapped the 4H demand zone, and broke two successive BOS on the 15m timeframe.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a 4H demand zone (order block) as the key HTF point of interest where price was expected to reverse.",
    "Step 2: Observed price sweep liquidity below equal lows (SSL) before entering the 4H demand zone, satisfying the liquidity sweep criterion for CHoCH.",
    "Step 3: On the 15m chart, confirmed price broke and closed above two successive bearish structures (BOS), forming a valid CHoCH from the 4H demand zone.",
    "Step 4: Zoomed into the 1m chart, waited for price to retest the 15m demand zone, then identified the new bullish order block created by the CHoCH impulse wave.",
    "Step 5: Placed a buy limit order at the top of the 1m order block, stop loss below the block’s low, and take-profit at the nearest swing high."
  ],
  "outcome": "Trade executed: buy limit order triggered, price reversed upward after mitigation, reached swing high target.",
  "lessons": "A high-probability CHoCH requires: (1) origin from HTF supply/demand zone, (2) prior liquidity sweep, and (3) break of ≥2 successive structures. Multi-timeframe alignment is essential for entry precision.",
